RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 2 400 Y Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 25300. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 126 lbs.; Older, 128 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VMR CANTADOR dueled, best. SIVAKO broke out, bumped, late kick. COUNTING STARS dueled, outfinished. PRINCE SHASTA pinched start, chased. BLUE EAGLE dueled, out kicked. NEXT EMOJI no menace. FAMOUS SHUES pinballed, veered in. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS POSTED INTO THE START OF THE RACE. A TRAINER OBJECTIONS WAS ALSO POSTED, THE TRAINER OF PRINCE SHASTA CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST SIVAKO FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE AT THE START, AFTER A STEWARD REVIEW THE CLAIM OF FOUL WAS DISALLOWED AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

BOURBON COWBOY mid pack, no factor. LOUISIANA EAGLE EYE off pace, blew turn. JUST ONE REASON no threat. EL BALTAZAR forced out turn. PER THE NEW MEXICO RACING COMMISSION, REVENANT EAGLE HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BITTEN sprinted to a clear lead to set all the pace and won going away. RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 14800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD HORSES THAT HAVE STARTED AT RUIDOSO IN 2023 AND DID NOT FINISH BETTER THAN 3RD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOISTEROUSLY IRISH pressed the pace from five wide then took the lead at the half mile marked and fended off the inside challenge in the stretch to prove best. DESERTROSE OFTEXAS moved between horses nearing the half mile marker to be forwardly placed and fought gamely down the stretch to prove second best. TIZ MY HOUR stalked the pace from three wide, made a mild bid on the turn and flattened out. DANSMETOTHENDOFLOV raced near the back early then steadily advanced through the turn, moved out to four wide in upper stretch to be best of the rest. BLUE LUNA WHO tracked the leaders through the turn then angled out to four wide in upper stretch to improve position. RELEASE THE GENIE prompted the pace to the half mile marker and faded. DESTINY WHO trailed the field through the turn, moved out to six wide in upper stretch and passed tiring rivals. MIDNIGHT SPECIAL T hopped at the start, then rushed up from five or six wide and tired. YOUR ADORABLE had a brief foot to the half mile marker and gave way. Race was Hand Timed.

ENTRY.COMMENT: near back, steady advance, 4wupper, best of rest

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 79. Allowance Purse 36700. FOR REGISTERED NEW MEXICO BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since June 10 Allowed 3 lbs. (Condition Eligibility Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: Z MARKS THE SPOT broke well, stalked the pace down the backstretch then moved up from three wide on the turn to engage the leader, took command at the top of the stretch and held on. SMARTSREALGOOD tracked the leader to the turn then made a mild bid to move up in early stretch and kept on to make a late surge to be second best. JEEPS STRIDE was off the pace while racing four wide, showed late effort in mid stretch and finished evenly. DIABOLICAL FIRE rushed up to press the pace from the two path then took the lead in mid turn and fought gamely to deep stretch and gave way. SARGE chased the leaders from the inside and was no match for the top four. RYDERS UP trailed the field and was out run. SHAME ON ROOSTER rushed up the rail to take the lead at the five furlong marker but was over taken in mid turn but kept on and appeared to take a bad step in the stretch, was pulled up, walked off. Race was Hand Timed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 10 5F Dirt CR: 77. Claiming Purse 14800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE MARCH 10, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JUNE 10, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BINALLOVERDRINKEN pressed the pace from the two path through the turn then took the lead at the five sixteenths pole, edged away and was kept to task in the stretch. GEE ETTA raced near the back down the backstretch from the inside then moved up from two or three wide on the turn, tipped out to five wide in upper stretch to make a late rally and proved second best. TIZ FOR REAL trailed the field to the turn then made a three wide bid on the turn and tipped out to mid track in the stretch for a rally. JUMPING JILL FLASH was off the pace from the two path but didn't make a bid while racing evenly. RAPPERS THIEF sprinted to the lead for a half and fought gamely to mid stretch but gave way. ELDORADO DREAM tracked the leaders from four wide on the backstretch then moved in to three wide on the turn to move up but faltered. WHERE'S FRANKIE was last away from the gate then was hustled along to be off the pace to the top of the stretch but was empty. DO ME A FAVOR was close up to the half mile marker then dropped back. Race was Hand Timed.
